      "Number of Applicable L4 Business Processes": "Unit: number of processes\n\nThis field represents the total number of applicable L3 processes within the relevant GC and domain.",
      "Number of L4 Business Processes in Draft State": "Unit: number of processes\n\nThis field shows the number of  L4 processes which are currenlty being updated (processes \"draft\" status). The field does not depend on the date in the filter. ",
      "Number of L4 Processes in Quality Review State": "Unit: number of processes\n\nThis field shows the number of  L4 processes which are currenlty being reviewed by the BPA Team (processes \"aproval in progress - Quality Review\" status). The field does not depend on the date in the filter. ",
      "Number of L4 Processes in Digital VP Sign-Off State": "Unit: number of processes\n\nThis field shows the number of  L4 processes which are currenlty being reviewed by Digital VPs (processes \"aproval in progress - Digital VP Sign-Off\" status). The field does not depend on the date in the filter. ",
      "Number of processes  Reviewed (Since date selected)": "Unit: number of processes\n\nThis field represents the number of L4 processes reviewed since the filtered date. If a process is reviewed multiple times within the selected period, it is counted only once. Reviewed means a review was added to the assessment card using the Process Review feature.\n(Date of Reviewed is when the User add a review to the Review Log)\n\n\nCalculation (#):\n(Total number of L3 processes reviewed within GC and Domain)\n\nThis field depends on the date selected in the filter.",
      "Number of processes  Re-assesed (Since date selected)": "Unit: number of processes\n\nThis field represents the number of L4 processes reassessed since the filtered date. If a process is reassessed multiple times within the selected period, it is counted only once. Reassessed means process got updated and published again. \n(Date of Reassesed is when the Digital VP approves it to be published).\n\n\nCalculation (#):\n(Total number of L3 processes reassesed within GC and Domain)\n\nThis field depends on the date selected in the filter.",
      "Number of Processes with Target Automation update (Since date Selected)": "Unit: number of processes\n\nThis field represents the number of L3 processes that have had either their Target Recommendation Remark or Target automation level field updated since the filtered date. If a process is reassessed multiple times within the selected period, it is counted only once. Target Recommendation Remark update means the field \"Target Recommendation Remark/explination\" was updated. \n(Date of Update is when the SME updated the Published Record).\n\nNote: We are only considering the Published records in the count.\n\nCalculation (#):\n(Total number of Published L3 processes that have their Target Recommendation Remark updated within GC and Domain)\n\nThis field depends on the date selected in the filter.",
      "Automation Parameters Data Completion (%)": "Unit: %\n\nThis field represents the  percentage of completed (i.e. filled) automation fields within the domain and GC,considering the most recent record, even if it's in draft or approval status.\n\nAutomation Fields consists of:\n\n2.4 Automation Maturity level \n2.5 Automation level \n2.6 Current Application/systems \n4.1 AI-Powered \nOngoing -Automation/Digital Initatives\n-Key Challenges & Automation Needs\n-Autonomous Usecase Enabled\n\n\n",
      "Manual Operations Parameters Data Completion (%)": "Unit: %\n\nThis field represents the  percentage of completed (i.e. filled) manual operation  fields within the domain and GC, considering the most recent record, even if it's in draft or approval status.\n\n(manual parameters)\n3.1 Process Frequency (per year)*\n3.2 Process Occurrence Number*\n3.4 Total Personnel, FTE*\n3.5 Total Process Duration, days*\n3.6 Manual Tasks Time, %*\n-Key Manual Activities",
      "Automation Level (%)": "Unit: %\n\nThis field represents the average automation maturity level in the domain and GC at the current time, considering the most recent record, even if it's in draft or approval status.\n",
      "Target Automation Level (%)": "Unit: %\n\nThis field represents the average target automation  level in the domain and GC at the current time, considering the most recent record, even if it's in draft or approval status.\n",
      "Cost of Manual effort , kAED": "Unit: In thousands, kAED\n\nThis calculated field represents the total sum of manual effort for the L3 processes within the domain and GC, with the total value divided to display in thousands.\n\nNote: Use the most recent L3 process value, even if it is in the approval or draft phase.",
      "Number of L3 Processes detailed with L4 Processes": null,
